    "message": "i18n: refactor compile catalog * fix: exclude node_modules from i18next-scanner extraction i18n: Update commands for message extraction and compilation * Since Transifex is used to manage translations, all we have   to provide is a .pot file as a source. This will be pushed   to Transifex. English is the default language, so this is generated on   extraction.When pulling from Transifex, .po files will be generated. * On package release, all available language files (.po) are  compiled   into .json files. These are then used by the application for lookup. * improved error handling and structure * use of async/await for better readability * add better logging and error messages * insure trailing newlines in en translation files and update   post-extract script * Cleaning up languages in package.json   that is created by init_catalog lang <lang> * docs: clarify instructions for pulling translations * update file headers to reflect correct project name and copyright"
